The Socioeconomic and Environment Advocacy Centre (SEAC) has been unveiled in Abuja in a ceremony witnessed by academics and civil servants from public agencies and the civil society The new non-governmental and non-profit organization with a registered office in Abuja is a Corporate Affairs Commission registered organisation with its Board of Trustees. According to the Director, Prof. Mohammed Bello Yunusa, the NGO was conceived to promote sustainable socio-economic development and environment in Nigeria.